      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not about \"small moments.\" i can't live on small moments when the entire foundation of my life has crumbled. it feels like i'm just a shell of a person waiting for the world to finally catch up and realize i'm not really here anymore. is it even worth trying to piece together something this broken? it feels more like a burden to everyone around me than a person worth helping.",
